{"questionId":"15614","questionHtml":"<p>Find the function, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> , that would define this footpath on the map.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0 - \\frac{7}{8}}}{{0 - \\frac{1}{2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>7</mn>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for correct substitution into gradient formula. Accept equivalent forms such as <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{7}{8} = \\frac{1}{2}m\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mn>8</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{7}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (1.75)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{7}{4}x\\,\\,\\left( {1.75x} \\right)\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.75</mn>\n      <mi>x